page.title: 03HUMAN GEOGRAPHY
page.content: The main determining features are the hills.The houses, roads, canal and railway have to run in between them. Most of the building and development is along the A281. Wonersh is quite small and is centered around a crossroad,whereas Bramley used to be small but is now 2km along the road. Blackheath is quite small because it is not built on an important road or rail link.It is also quite high up.Even though the canal and railway have been closed, most of the development is still along the A281.
